{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775865008397,"sessionID":"ses_28633740bffefnBB9BsCX1uTgC","part":{"id":"prt_d79cd90d400168IPM9mJMrqxj7","messageID":"msg_d79cc95690013ZKlfXu3yPyKRC","sessionID":"ses_28633740bffefnBB9BsCX1uTgC","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-82d6716de7714e2ca717be6a098d7890","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# AR-020: CLI pack е‘Ҫд»Ө вҖ” Design\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `pack` command in the AgentCube CLI is responsible for validating and preparing an agent workspace, merging CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generating a `Dockerfile`, and reporting paths to the packaged artifacts.\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Source Root:** `/tmp/agentcube-ref/cmd/cli/`\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n| Component | Location | Responsibility |\n|-----------|----------|----------------|\n| `PackRuntime` | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Core packing logic implementation |\n| `MetadataService` | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Metadata loading, saving, and validation |\n| `MetadataOptions` | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | Dataclass for CLI option parsing |\n| `pack` command | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer command definition and CLI entry point |\n\n### Data Flow\n\n```\nCLI Options вҶ’ MetadataOptions вҶ’ PackRuntime.pack()\n                                      вҶ“\n                     _validate_workspace_structure()\n                                      вҶ“\n                      _load_or_create_metadata()\n                                      вҶ“\n                      _apply_option_overrides()\n                                      вҶ“\n                    _validate_language_compatibility()\n                                      вҶ“\n                         _process_dependencies()\n                                      вҶ“\n                         _generate_dockerfile()\n                                      вҶ“\n                     _update_pack_metadata()\n                                      вҶ“\n                         _prepare_output_path()\n                                      вҶ“\n                            Return result\n```\n\n## Detailed Implementation\n\n### 1. CLI Command (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n\n```python\ndef pack(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n    agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n    language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n    port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n    build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n    description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n    output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Package an agent workspace by validating structure and generating metadata.\"\"\"\n```\n\n**Command behavior:**\n- Resolves workspace path relative to current directory if not absolute\n- Creates `PackRuntime` instance with verbose flag\n- Collects options into a dictionary\n- Calls `PackRuntime.pack(workspace_path, **options)`\n- Handles exceptions via `_handle_error(e, \"pack\", verbose)`\n\n### 2. PackRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`)\n\n#### Class Structure\n\n```python\nclass PackRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.logger = get_logger(__name__, level=logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n```\n\n#### Main Method: `pack()`\n\n```python\ndef pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Package an agent workspace.\n\n    Returns:\n        Dict containing:\n        - agent_name: str\n        - workspace_path: str (absolute path)\n        - metadata_path: str\n        - dockerfile_path: Optional[str]\n        - language: str\n        - entrypoint: str\n        - port: int\n    \"\"\"\n    with Progress() as progress:\n        task = progress.add_task(\"[cyan]Packing workspace...\", total=100)\n\n        progress.update(task, advance=10)\n        self._validate_workspace_structure(workspace_path)\n\n        progress.update(task, advance=20)\n        metadata = self._load_or_create_metadata(workspace_path, options)\n\n        progress.update(task, advance=20)\n        metadata = self._apply_option_overrides(metadata, options)\n\n        progress.update(task, advance=10)\n        self._validate_language_compatibility(workspace_path, metadata)\n\n        progress.update(task, advance=15)\n        self._process_dependencies(workspace_path, metadata)\n\n        progress.update(task, advance=15)\n        dockerfile_path = self._generate_dockerfile(workspace_path, metadata)\n\n        progress.update(task, advance=10)\n        self._update_pack_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, dockerfile_path)\n\n        progress.update(task, advance=10)\n        output_path = self._prepare_output_path(workspace_path, options.get(\"output\"))\n\n    return {\n        \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n        \"workspace_path\": str(output_path),\n        \"metadata_path\": str(output_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"),\n        \"dockerfile_path\": str(dockerfile_path) if dockerfile_path else None,\n        \"language\": metadata.language,\n        \"entrypoint\": metadata.entrypoint,\n        \"port\": metadata.port,\n    }\n```\n\n#### Helper Methods\n\n**`_validate_workspace_structure()`**\n- Validates `workspace_path` exists and is a directory\n- Raises `ValueError` with clear message if not\n\n**`_load_or_create_metadata()`**\n- Attempts to load existing metadata from `agent_metadata.yaml`\n- Falls back to `agent.yaml` then `metadata.yaml` if primary missing\n- Creates new `AgentMetadata` if no existing file found\n- Infers defaults: `language=\"python\"`, `port=8080`, `build_mode=\"local\"`\n\n**`_apply_option_overrides()`**\n- Merges CLI options into metadata\n- Priority: CLI options > existing metadata > defaults\n- Creates new `AgentMetadata` instance to ensure validation\n\n**`_validate_language_compatibility()`**\n- Validates Python workspace: requires at least one `*.py` file\n- Validates Java workspace: requires `pom.xml` file\n- Raises `ValueError` with specific message per language\n\n**`_process_dependencies()`**\n- Python: Validates `requirements.txt` exists, creates if missing with minimal content\n- Java: Validates `pom.xml` exists (already checked in compatibility)\n\n**`_generate_dockerfile()`**\n- Skips if `metadata.build_mode == \"cloud\"`\n- Calls language-specific generator based on `metadata.language`\n- Returns path to generated Dockerfile or None\n\n**`_generate_python_dockerfile()`**\n- Base image: `python:3.11-slim`\n- Workdir: `/app`\n- Copy requirements and install\n- Copy application code\n- Expose port from metadata\n- Entrypoint from metadata\n\n**`_generate_java_dockerfile()`**\n- Base image: `openjdk:17-jdk-slim`\n- Workdir: `/app`\n- Copy `pom.xml` and run Maven build\n- Copy JAR from target\n- Expose port from metadata\n- Entrypoint: `java -jar {jar_name}`\n\n**`_update_pack_metadata()`**\n- Saves metadata to `agent_metadata.yaml` using `MetadataService`\n- Excludes None fields from output\n- Updates dockerfile_path in metadata\n\n**`_prepare_output_path()`**\n- Returns workspace_path if output not specified\n- Creates output directory if doesn't exist\n- Returns absolute path\n\n**`_infer_entrypoint()`**\n- Python: `python main.py` if `main.py` exists\n- Java: `java -jar target/*.jar`\n- Default: metadata.entrpoint or raise error\n\n### 3. MetadataService (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n\n```python\nclass MetadataService:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.logger = get_logger(__name__, level=logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n\n    def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n        \"\"\"Load metadata from workspace with fallback order.\"\"\"\n        for filename in [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]:\n            metadata_path = workspace_path / filename\n            if metadata_path.exists():\n                with open(metadata_path, \"r\") as f:\n                    data = yaml.safe_load(f)\n                return AgentMetadata(**data)\n        raise FileNotFoundError(\"No metadata file found in workspace\")\n\n    def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Save metadata to agent_metadata.yaml.\"\"\"\n        metadata_path = workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n        with open(metadata_path, \"w\") as f:\n            yaml.dump(\n                metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True),\n                f,\n                default_flow_style=False,\n                indent=2,\n                sort_keys=False,\n            )\n\n    def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Validate workspace structure based on language.\"\"\"\n        metadata = self.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n        if metadata.language == \"python\":\n            self._validate_python_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n        elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n            self._validate_java_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n        return True\n\n    def _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Validate Python workspace has at least one .py file.\"\"\"\n        py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n        if not py_files:\n            raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n\n    def _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Validate Java workspace has pom.xml.\"\"\"\n        if not (workspace_path / \"pom.xml\").exists():\n            raise ValueError(\"Java workspace requires pom.xml\")\n```\n\n### 4. MetadataOptions (`agentcube/models/pack_models.py`)\n\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass MetadataOptions:\n    \"\"\"Options for pack command CLI arguments.\"\"\"\n    agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n    language: Optional[str] = \"python\"\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n    port: Optional[int] = 8080\n    build_mode: Optional[str] = \"local\"\n    requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n    description: Optional[str] = None\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n    registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n\n    @classmethod\n    def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n        \"\"\"Create from CLI options dict.\"\"\"\n        return cls(\n            agent_name=options.get(\"agent_name\"),\n            language=options.get(\"language\"),\n            entrypoint=options.get(\"entrypoint\"),\n            port=options.get(\"port\"),\n            build_mode=options.get(\"build_mode\"),\n            description=options.get(\"description\"),\n            workspace_manager_url=options.get(\"workspace_manager_url\"),\n            router_url=options.get(\"router_url\"),\n            readiness_probe_path=options.get(\"readiness_probe_path\"),\n            readiness_probe_port=options.get(\"readiness_probe_port\"),\n        )\n```\n\n### 5. AgentMetadata (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n\n```python\nclass AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n    \"\"\"Agent metadata model with validation.\"\"\"\n    agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n    description: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Human-readable summary\")\n    language: str = Field(\"python\", description=\"Programming language used\")\n    entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n    port: int = Field(8080, description=\"Port exposed by the agent runtime\")\n    build_mode: str = Field(\"local\", description=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\")\n    region: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Deployment region\")\n    version: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Semantic version string for publishing\")\n    image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Container image information\")\n    auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Authentication configuration\")\n    requirements_file: Optional[str] = Field(\"requirements.txt\", description=\"Python dependency file\")\n    registry_url: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry URL for image publishing\")\n    registry_username: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry username\")\n    registry_password: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry password\")\n    agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent endpoint URL\")\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Workload Manager\")\n    router_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Router\")\n    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Path for the readiness probe\")\n    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = Field(None, description=\"Port for the readiness probe\")\n    agent_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent ID assigned by AgentCube\")\n    session_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"The session ID for the agent\")\n    k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Kubernetes deployment information\")\n\n    @field_validator(\"language\")\n    @classmethod\n    def validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Validate language is supported.\"\"\"\n        v = v.lower()\n        if v not in [\"python\", \"java\"]:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported language: {v}. Supported: python, java\")\n        return v\n\n    @field_validator(\"build_mode\")\n    @classmethod\n    def validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Validate build mode is supported.\"\"\"\n        v = v.lower()\n        if v not in [\"local\", \"cloud\"]:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported build mode: {v}. Supported: local, cloud\")\n        return v\n\n    @field_validator(\"port\")\n    @classmethod\n    def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Validate port is in valid range.\"\"\"\n        if not 1 <= v <= 65535:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Port must be between 1 and 65535, got {v}\")\n        return v\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Flow\n\n```python\ntry:\n    result = runtime.pack(workspace_path, **options)\n    # Print success with Rich console\n    console.print(f\"[green]вң“[/green] Agent packed successfully: {result['agent_name']}\")\n    console.print(f\"  Workspace: [cyan]{result['workspace_path']}[/cyan]\")\n    console.print(f\"  Metadata: [cyan]{result['metadata_path']}[/cyan]\")\n    if result['dockerfile_path']:\n        console.print(f\"  Dockerfile: [cyan]{result['dockerfile_path']}[/cyan]\")\nexcept Exception as e:\n    _handle_error(e, \"pack\", verbose)\n```\n\n### `_handle_error()` Implementation\n\n```python\ndef _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Handle command errors with optional traceback.\"\"\"\n    console = Console()\n    console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}:[/red] {e}\")\n    if verbose:\n        import traceback\n        console.print(traceback.format_exc())\n    raise typer.Exit(1)\n```\n\n### Common Error Scenarios\n\n| Error | Condition | Message |\n|-------|-----------|---------|\n| `ValueError` | Workspace doesn't exist | \"Workspace directory does not exist: {path}\" |\n| `ValueError` | No Python files | \"No Python files found in workspace\" |\n| `ValueError` | No pom.xml for Java | \"Java workspace requires pom.xml\" |\n| `ValueError` | Invalid language | \"Unsupported language: {lang}. Supported: python, java\" |\n| `ValueError` | Invalid build mode | \"Unsupported build mode: {mode}. Supported: local, cloud\" |\n| `ValueError` | Invalid port | \"Port must be between 1 and 65535, got {port}\" |\n| `PydanticValidationError` | Invalid metadata type | Validation errors from Pydantic |\n\n## CLI Output Format\n\n### Success Output\n\n```\nвң“ Agent packed successfully: my-agent\n  Workspace: /path/to/workspace\n  Metadata: /path/to/workspace/agent_metadata.yaml\n  Dockerfile: /path/to/workspace/Dockerfile\n```\n\n### Error Output (non-verbose)\n\n```\nError pack: No Python files found in workspace\n```\n\n### Error Output (verbose)\n\n```\nError pack: No Python files found in workspace\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"...\", line ..., in pack\n    self._validate_python_workspace(workspace_path)\n  ...\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Runtime Dependencies (from `pyproject.toml`)\n\n- `typer[all]>=0.9.0` - CLI framework\n- `pydantic>=2.0.0` - Data validation\n- `pyyaml>=6.0` - YAML parsing/writing\n- `rich>=13.0.0` - Terminal output formatting\n\n### Optional Dependencies\n\n- `docker>=6.0.0` - Used by `DockerService` (not in pack command)\n\n## Test Coverage\n\n### Unit Tests Required\n\n| Component | Test Cases |\n|-----------|------------|\n| `PackRuntime.pack()` | - Happy path with valid workspace<br>- Workspace validation failure<br>- Metadata loading fallback<br>- Option override merging<br>- Language-specific validation<br>- Dockerfile generation |\n| `_validate_workspace_structure()` | - Existing directory<br>- Non-existent path<br>- File instead of directory |\n| `_load_or_create_metadata()` | - Load existing metadata<br>- Fallback to agent.yaml<br>- Fallback to metadata.yaml<br>- Create new metadata<br>- Infer defaults |\n| `_apply_option_overrides()` | - Override all fields<br>- Partial override<br>- No override |\n| `_validate_language_compatibility()` | - Valid Python workspace<br>- Python workspace with no .py files<br>- Valid Java workspace<br>- Java workspace without pom.xml |\n| `_generate_dockerfile()` | - Python local build<br>- Java local build<br>- Cloud build (skip) |\n| `MetadataService` | - Load metadata from all filenames<br>- Save metadata with exclude_none<br>- Validate workspace per language |\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n- End-to-end pack command with workspace\n- CLI option parsing and passing\n- Error handling flow\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Path validation**: Ensure workspace path is within expected directory to prevent path traversal\n2. **Dockerfile generation**: Validate port range to prevent invalid container configuration\n3. **Metadata persistence**: Exclude sensitive fields (auth tokens) from saved metadata if not needed\n4. **Command injection**: Validate and sanitize entrypoint command before writing to Dockerfile\n\n## Future Enhancements\n\n1. Support for additional languages (Node.js, Go, etc.)\n2. Multi-stage Dockerfile generation for optimized images\n3. Dependency analysis to include only required packages\n4. Workspace templates for quick-start\n5. Interactive mode for metadata creation\n6. Workspace validation rules extensible via plugins","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/design.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/design.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775865008388,"end":1775865008393}}}}
